<tr>
<td colspan="2" align="center" style="width:100%; font-size: 1.25em; white-space: nowrap;"><b><span class="fn org">Golan Heights</span><br />
<span class="nickname">רמת הגולן<br />
هضبة الجولان</span></b></td>
</tr>
<tr class="mergedtoprow">
<td colspan="2" style="text-align:center;background:#cddeff;">—&#160;&#160;<b>Disputed territory controlled by Syria 1944-67 then by Israel since 1967</b>&#160;&#160;—</td>
</tr>
<tr class="mergedrow">
<td colspan="2" style="text-align: center;">
<div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Golan_heights_rel89B.jpg" class="image" title="Sites on the Golan in blue are Jewish communities. Sites on the Golan in black are Druze communities. Areas of the Golan controlled by Israel are light-coloured while those under Syrian control are grey. The Golan Heights are surrounded by four countries: Lebanon, Syria, Jordan, and Israel."><img alt="Sites on the Golan in blue are Jewish communities. Sites on the Golan in black are Druze communities. Areas of the Golan controlled by Israel are light-coloured while those under Syrian control are grey. The Golan Heights are surrounded by four countries: Lebanon, Syria, Jordan, and Israel." src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/91/Golan_heights_rel89B.jpg/300px-Golan_heights_rel89B.jpg" width="300" height="384" border="0" /></a></div>
<small>Sites on the Golan in blue are Jewish communities. Sites on the Golan in black are Druze communities. Areas of the Golan controlled by Israel are light-coloured while those under Syrian control are grey. The Golan Heights are surrounded by four countries: <a href="/wiki/Lebanon" title="Lebanon">Lebanon</a>, <a href="/wiki/Syria" title="Syria">Syria</a>, <a href="/wiki/Jordan" title="Jordan">Jordan</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Israel" title="Israel">Israel</a>.</small></td>
</tr>
<tr class="mergedtoprow">
