<p><a name="Economy" id="Economy"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Golan_Heights&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Economy">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Economy</span></h2>
<p>In addition to the importance of water resources, the Golan Heights also has Israel's only <a href="/wiki/Skiing" title="Skiing">ski</a> resort, near <a href="/wiki/Mount_Hermon" title="Mount Hermon">Mount Hermon</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-BBC_ME_Country_Profile_12-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-BBC_ME_Country_Profile-12" title=""><span>[</span>13<span>]</span></a></sup> Winemaking is a major and <a href="/wiki/Israeli_wine#Wine_revolution" title="Israeli wine">highly successful</a> industry. Cattle graze on the upland plateau. The area is also popular for hiking.</p>
<p>In 2005 the Golan Heights had a population of approximately 38,900, including approximately 19,300 <a href="/wiki/Druze" title="Druze">Druze</a>, 16,500 <a href="/wiki/Jew" title="Jew">Jews</a>, and 2,100 <a href="/wiki/Muslim" title="Muslim">Muslims</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-CBS_13-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CBS-13" title=""><span>[</span>14<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><a name="Current_status" id="Current_status"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Golan_Heights&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Current status">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Current status</span></h2>
